snippet: American diplomats contacted Muslim Brotherhood leaders to try to persuade them to re-enter the political process, an Islamist briefed on one of the conversations said.
abstract: Muslim Brotherhood officials say that American diplomats have sought to persuade the group to accept ouster of Pres Mohamed Morsi and re-enter political process.

byline.original: By DAVID D. KIRKPATRICK and KAREEM FAHIM
byline.contributor: Mayy El Sheikh and Asmaa Al Zohairy contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: American diplomats contacted Muslim Brotherhood leaders to try to persuade them to re-enter the political process, an Islamist briefed on one of the conversations said.

headline.main: Brotherhood Says U.S. Diplomats Urged It to Accept Ouster of Morsi
